  "text": "interval [φ i , φ i + 2πkd/N (mod2π)]. A given θ j will potentially be contained in the intervals for many different windows, though it is unlikely to coincide exactly with any of the frames in each window, so we use linear interpolation to fill in a frame corresponding to θ j in each window overlapping it. The frame at angle φ j is taken as the median of all interpolated frames. Furthermore, we only use interpolated frames that are a user-prescribed amount F away in time for each given reordered frame, to avoid ghosting artifacts [CITATION_1] .",
